<treatmentCitationGroup id="A3FE8441FFBDFFC0FF49FBC8B6DDFBFF" box="[166,706,1116,1139]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">
<treatmentCitation id="024F857EFFBDFFC0FF49FBC8B612FBFF" author="Wunderlich, J." box="[166,525,1117,1139]" page="362" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" year="1992">
<taxonomicName id="44EED8ECFFBDFFC0FF49FBC8B612FBFF" authority=": Wunderlich, 1992: 362" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityPageNumber="362" authorityYear="1992" box="[166,525,1117,1139]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Meta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barretti">
<emphasis id="B19A7F7DFFBDFFC0FF49FBC8B539FBFE" box="[166,294,1117,1139]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Meta barretti</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="E77FDE9EFFBDFFC0FEDFFBCBB612FBFF" author="Wunderlich, J." box="[304,525,1117,1139]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" pagination="1 - 619" refId="ref5218" refString="Wunderlich, J. 1992. Die Spinnen-Fauna der Makaronesischen Inseln: Taxonomie, Okologie, Biogeographie und Evolution. Beitrage zur Araneologie, 1, 1 - 619." type="journal article" year="1992">Wunderlich, 1992: 362</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
, f. 327‒329 (♂, 
<specimenCount id="95E868E6FFBDFFC0FD4AFBCAB6ABFBFF" box="[677,692,1116,1139]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
).
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8351A36FFFBDFFC0FF34FB03B53FFABC" blockId="4.[166,1225,1173,1328]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">
Note. The species was described and is known from Madeira only (
<bibRefCitation id="E77FDE9EFFBDFFC0FBC2FB03B0A3FB3C" author="WSC" box="[1069,1212,1173,1200]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" refId="ref5187" refString="WSC, 2017. World Spider Catalog. Natural History Museum Bern. (http: // wsc. nmbe. ch, version 18.0; accessed: 28.02.2017)." type="url" year="2017">WSC, 2017</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="E77FDE9EFFBDFFC0FF49FB23B599FB5C" author="Wunderlich, J." box="[166,390,1205,1232]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" pagination="44 - 139" refId="ref5248" refString="Wunderlich, J. 2008. Descriptions of fossil spider (Araneae) taxa mainly in Baltic amber, as well as on certain related extant taxa. Beitrage zur Araneologie, 5, 44 - 139." type="journal article" year="2008">Wunderlich (2008)</bibRefCitation>
already doubted its belonging to 
<taxonomicName id="44EED8ECFFBDFFC0FCEDFB23B720FB42" baseAuthorityName="WSC" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[770,831,1205,1230]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Meta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B19A7F7DFFBDFFC0FCEDFB23B720FB42" box="[770,831,1205,1230]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Meta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and mentioned that it may belong to 
<taxonomicName id="44EED8ECFFBDFFC0FF2BFB42B52CFB62" authorityName="Chamberlin &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="1941" box="[196,307,1236,1262]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Metellina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B19A7F7DFFBDFFC0FF2BFB42B52CFB62" box="[196,307,1236,1262]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Metellina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Judging from the description and illustration provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="E77FDE9EFFBDFFC0FC0EFB43B0DCFB7C" author="Wunderlich, J." box="[993,1219,1237,1264]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" pagination="1 - 619" refId="ref5218" refString="Wunderlich, J. 1992. Die Spinnen-Fauna der Makaronesischen Inseln: Taxonomie, Okologie, Biogeographie und Evolution. Beitrage zur Araneologie, 1, 1 - 619." type="journal article" year="1992">Wunderlich (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, this species certainly must be transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="44EED8ECFFBDFFC0FD44FB63B705FA83" authorityName="Chamberlin &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="1941" box="[683,794,1269,1295]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Metellina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B19A7F7DFFBDFFC0FD44FB63B705FA83" box="[683,794,1269,1295]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Metellina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and therefore a new combination is suggested.
</paragraph>
